article_text:
MALIN, India—Rescue workers dug through tons of mud and debris on Friday, searching for people buried when a massive landslide engulfed a village in western India earlier in the week.

Four people, including a woman and her three-month-old child, were pulled alive from the muck on Wednesday, but no survivors have been found since. More than 100...
